Reasoning: The paper deals with performance modeling of distributed-memory applications, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the impact of noise on the performance of the system, which is related to Performance Analysis and Optimization (cs.PF). The study of delay propagation and overlapping mechanisms involves analyzing the communication patterns of the system, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the interaction between delays and their decay under increased noise levels, which is related to Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the collective phenomena that manifest themselves in distributed-memory parallel applications, which is related to Software Engineering (cs.SE).
